  "prompt": "Is calibri with font size 9 good for resume?",
  "response": "Using the right font and size is crucial for creating a professional and readable resume. Let's break down the considerations for using **Calibri with a font size of 9** on your resume:\n\n### **Calibri as a Resume Font**\n\n**Pros:**\n1. **Modern and Clean:** Calibri is a sans-serif font that offers a contemporary and uncluttered look, which can make your resume appear fresh and organized.\n2. **Readability:** It\u2019s designed for clear on-screen display, ensuring that your resume is easy to read both digitally and in print.\n3. **Widely Accepted:** As the default font for Microsoft Office applications since 2007, many recruiters are accustomed to seeing Calibri, which can be a safe choice.\n\n**Cons:**\n1. **Commonality:** Because Calibri is a default and widely used font, your resume might not stand out as much compared to those using more unique typography.\n2. **Industry Preferences:** Some industries, particularly more traditional ones like finance or law, may prefer classic fonts like Times New Roman or Garamond.\n\n### **Font Size 9 Considerations**\n\n**Pros:**\n- **Space Efficiency:** Using a smaller font size like 9 can allow you to include more information on a single page, which is beneficial if you have extensive experience.\n\n**Cons:**\n1. **Readability Issues:** Font size 9 is generally considered small for resumes. It might be difficult for recruiters to read, especially when printed on paper.\n2. **Professional Appearance:** Smaller fonts can make your resume look cramped and less professional, potentially deterring recruiters from thoroughly reviewing your information.\n\n### **Best Practices for Resume Fonts and Sizes**\n\n1. **Font Choice:**\n   - **Safe Options:** Calibri, Arial, Helvetica, Garamond, and Times New Roman are all reputable choices.\n   - **Unique Yet Professional:** Fonts like Cambria, Verdana, or Tahoma offer a bit of uniqueness while maintaining professionalism.\n\n2. **Font Size:**\n   - **Main Text:** Aim for a font size between **10 and 12 points**. This range ensures readability without appearing too large.\n   - **Headers:** You can use a slightly larger font size (12-14 points) for section headings to create a clear hierarchy.\n\n3. **Consistency:**\n   - Maintain consistent font styles and sizes throughout your resume. Use bolding or italics sparingly to highlight important sections or information.\n\n4. **Spacing and Margins:**\n   - Use adequate spacing (such as 1-inch margins) to ensure your resume doesn\u2019t look cluttered.\n   - Utilize bullet points and sufficient line spacing to enhance readability.\n\n5. **Content Over Style:**\n   - While aesthetics are important, the content of your resume should take precedence. Clear, concise, and relevant information will have a more significant impact than font choices alone.\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nWhile **Calibri** is a solid and professional font choice for resumes, using it at **font size 9** is generally **not recommended** due to readability concerns. Opting for a slightly larger font size (between 10 and 12 points) will make your resume easier to read and more visually appealing to recruiters. Always prioritize clarity and professionalism to ensure your resume effectively showcases your qualifications.",
